{{see|säga|såga}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Old Norse (Icelandic) ''[[saga#Icelandic|saga]]'', cognate with English ''[[saw#Etymology 2|saw]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'sɑ:gə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An Old Norse prose narrative of Iceland or Norway, especially dealing with family or social histories and legends
# Something with the qualities of such a saga; an [[epic]], a long [[story]].

